(200, 325, 'Kick-off Infor LN ERP System Implementation at PT Sanoh with PT BSI', 'pt-sanoh-using-erp-infor-ln', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\">PT Sanoh Indonesia is established since 1976. PT Sanoh is mainly supporting the automotive industry. Their main customers are some of the big brands of Japanese automotive vehicles such as Toyota, Daihatsu, Nissan, Hino Mitsubishi, Astra Honda Motor, Kawasaki, and Suzuki. PT Sanoh Indonesia has three divisions which are Chassis, Brazing, and Plastic. In the Chassis department, they mainly produce fuel tubes and brake tubes. Brazing division produces car engines, radiator tubes, oil level gauge, and others, whereas the plastic department produces fuel tubes from plastic.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/banners/PT%20Sanoh%20Indonesia%2001.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Indonesia’s Automotive Industry 4.0 Symposium\" title=\"Indonesia’s Automotive Industry 4.0 Symposium\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">PT Sanoh Indonesia chose to implement the ERP system in their company called Infor LN. They also chose to partner with PT Bisnis Sistem Indonesia (PT BSI) to implement the system smoothly into their company. PT BSI is one of the companies that offer ERP solutions. PT BSI has been providing clients with successful ERP Infor LN since 1998. Since then PT BSI continues to build a good reputation ever since.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/banners/PT%20Sanoh%20Indonesia%2002.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Indonesia’s Automotive Industry 4.0 Symposium\" title=\"Indonesia’s Automotive Industry 4.0 Symposium Infor\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The reason why PT Sanoh Indonesia chose to implement Infor LN in their company is the accountability and the zero complaints from one of the subsidiaries of PT Sanoh in Thailand. During the visit of representatives of PT Sanoh Indonesia in Thailand, they concluded that Infor is one the best choice for ERP implementation in PT Sanoh Indonesia.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Before deciding on implementing ERP, the production sector of PT Sanoh Indonesia suffers a daily struggle which is items that are coded inconsistently. Due to this issue, in the scenario where they receive an order from the customer, the marketing team uses the item code based on what is written on the order slip. However, as time passed and the engineering team does trial and errors the code of the same item changed. Unfortunately, when the code changes, the engineers do not inform the other divisions about this matter. At the end, when it is time for mass production, the item that the engineering team request is not the same as what it is originally registered as. This problem causes a lot of confusion and could lead to money loss. Because the item codes are not consistent, perception and understanding about item codes differ per division.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">PT Sanoh Indonesia saw the problem as an adverse, inefficient and potentially expand production cost. Therefore they quickly looked for a precise solution to the problem using a system that integrates among departments. The system is called ERP.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Because of the capacity and what ERP is promised to be capable of, PT Sanoh Indonesia hopes that ERP could tackle the problem stated above and result in all items and jobs starting from warehouse to finished product to be sent to the customer are recorded properly with one data used in a bill. So, there is no more confusion regarding part code number, part name, customer, invoice, and payment. Each department will report their data to the software and all department could see the data posted there.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After surveying several companies they found that Infor is easy to use and user-friendly. According to Ibu Dian, from an accounting perspective of PT Sanoh Indonesia, despite having a system already, it is not optimized to its full potential because it is not integrated into the flow of production. Therefore they chose to implement the system for the purpose of simplifying the process of auditing from the tax office and internal auditing. PT BSI is trusted to implement ERP system at PT Sanoh because they claimed that the initial support from PT BSI to them is very good so therefore they feel more comfortable.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information about the solution please contact our phone at +6221 304 90008 or <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Whatsapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WhatsApp +628111221789</a> (Chat Only) or our email at ptbsi@ptbsi.co.id<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 87, '2020-03-05 04:22:07', 862, '', '2021-03-02 04:00:12', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2020-03-05 05:17:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 15, 0, 10, 'PT Sanoh, Implementation ERP, PT BSI, Infor LN, How to Solve the problem with ERP, ERP System Implementation. erp, erp software, erp system', 'Recently PT BSI secured a partnership with PT Sanoh Indonesia. PT Sanoh hopes that Infor LN would eliminate the difficulties that they once had before implementing Infor LN', 1, 3658, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(201, 326, 'The Importance of an Integrated Business Process in Automotive/Manufacturing Industry', 'integrated-automotive-manufacturing-industry-system', '', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/banners/foto1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The Importance of an Integrated Business Process in Automotive/Manufacturing Industry\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A business process is a collection of structured jobs or tasks that are linked to each other that ends when a service is delivered or a product reaches to a client. Among <strong> manufacturing industries</strong>, the <strong> automotive industry </strong> emphasizes on the assembly line of automotive that requires many spare parts and personnel. Every step of the job requires great attention to detail. Starting from product design to production, all have to be united in order for smooth production and not come to a halt.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Since each production in the automotive industry step requires a great amount of detail, an <strong>integrated factory system</strong> is needed. Because even from the designing process, components of the vehicle already need to be taken account for. Depending on the size and model of the vehicle, the components and spare parts needed are different from each other.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This producing complexity is at the mercy of the purchasing team. The purchasing team is in charge of purchasing all of the various spare parts that the designer requested for mock-ups and for mass production. The purchasing team also has to take into account spares in case some are defects. Before the purchasing team orders, the warehouse division informs the purchasing team of what items are in stock, to optimize what is already owned.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/banners/foto2.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The Importance of an Integrated Business Process in Automotive/Manufacturing Industry\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Every department must communicate with each other so the production is smooth. In the factory that needs a highly detailed job, what happens if they do not communicate with each other? Each department is waiting for each other to make a decision. The demands of each department are not met. Deadlines are forcibly pushed back. Possibly, loss of money as well. Since vehicles are released every single year, automotive companies compete with each other to sell more of their vehicles. If the release of the vehicles is pushed back because of a problem in the production department, customers will be drawn to purchase the vehicle from another company.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/banners/foto3.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The Importance of an Integrated Business Process in Automotive/Manufacturing Industry\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When everything is accurate and efficient it would <strong> reduce the additional production cost</strong>. Also, the data on the system could be accessed by all of the departments. The data could be used by the other departments as a guide to making a decision and forecasting sales and purchases items.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To <strong> increase the efficiency </strong> and productivity of the automotive factory, a <strong>new technology</strong> that is an <strong>integrated manufacturing factory system </strong> is needed. The system that is efficient, and increases productivity. The data of the warehouse division could be accessed by the purchasing team. Information is shared via the cloud service of the ERP software. Because information is shared via cloud and easily accessible, each department could make faster decisions based on the information shared such as forecasting sales and purchases items. The system also <strong> saves energy </strong> as it could optimize the capacity of the factory to make as many products as possible, without compromising on energy normally used.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/banners/foto4.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The Importance of an Integrated Business Process in Automotive/Manufacturing Industry\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">ERP system enables a company to integrate systems inside the company and automizing processes in the company. The implementation of ERP in the company would result in increased efficiency and productivity as all information is shared and work progress would be easily tracked. On top of that, the software could be accessed just by the touch of the fingertips.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A leading ERP software provider in Indonesia, PT Bisnis Sistem Indonesia (BSI) has been supplying clients with successful ERP system implementation in companies since 1998.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">PT BSI offers Infor LN that resolves the problems of companies in the automotive industry. Tackling the complexity of the production process and optimizing cost &amp; production are some of the things that Infor LN resolves.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Infor LN is:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Easily accessible</li>\r\n<li>User-friendly</li>\r\n<li>Easy to adopt into the company</li>\r\n<li>Has been testified to significantly reduce the time and effort that is needed to maintain all the processes in the company and eliminates the errors that are caused by data maintenance.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In conclusion, an integrated business is important in the automotive manufacturing industry. The company needs to implement an ERP system because the ERP system will enable more efficient communication and integrates data.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information about the solution please contact our phone at +6221 304 90008 or <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Whatsapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WhatsApp +628111221789</a> (Chat Only) or our email at ptbsi@ptbsi.co.id</p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 86, '2020-03-13 02:48:40', 862, '', '2021-03-02 03:58:32', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2020-03-13 03:45:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 35, 0, 23, 'integrated factory system, integrated manufacturing factory system, erp, erp system, software erp terbaik, sistem erp perusahaan, sistem erp terintegrasi, sistem erp pada perusahaan', 'In a factory that requires highly detailed jobs from designing to the production process, it is important to have an integrated business process in the automotive industry.\r\n', 1, 656, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(202, 327, 'Two Reasons why Enterprise Business Need ERP System', 'two-reasons-why-enterprise-business-need-erp-system', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/banners/pict1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"ERP needs in huge scale company\" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Unable to monitor everything because of such a huge scale company</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Due to the large scale of the company, having many subsidiaries and employing thousands of people, challenges may arise. One of them would be tracking the work progress of the hundreds and thousands of employees across the company. It is not easy to manage a large number of people, furthermore, some of the employees also work for the subsidiaries scattered around the world. Tracking the work progress of each headquarters is not an easy task in this scenario.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Risk-management based on a large data</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Because an enterprise business is a huge business, therefore the data that are managed are very complex, especially when the company has subsidiaries that are spread in a few locations.</p>\r\n<p>The enterprise company needs a system to manage a large amount of data, so the management will minimalize risks in errors such as data processing, data analysis, until the decision made based on the data.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Furthermore, the complex data should be read in real-time in order for management to determine a decision properly. If data managing in a company of enterprise-scale still uses a manual system, it can be confirmed that there will be plenty of errors in data management.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/banners/pict2.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> Enterprise needs ERP </strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>The challenges stated above are the reason why enterprises need to implement an ERP system. ERP system is used by organizations to manage and integrate information inside the divisions of the business enterprise and automize methods in the organization. ERP in the shape of software allows integrating all the tactics that are required to run the enterprise smoothly.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>The software is created in order that producing a product becomes efficient and streamline so that it will fulfill the needs of customers fast and accurately. ERP pre-plans what is supposed to be done based on collective records about each team or division.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>The implementation of ERP in the company would result in an increase in efficiency and productivity as all information is shared and work progress would be easily tracked. On top of that, the software could be accessed just by the touch of the fingertips.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> The benefits of implementing ERP </strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>With the implementation of ERP in the enterprise, the company will <strong> save more money </strong> because of the optimization of production costs calculated precisely through the software. <strong>Improved productivity</strong> is achievable because all data are integrated it becomes efficient to access the data and making it faster to proceed to the next job.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>After ERP is implemented to a company, <strong> improved collaboration </strong> will be achieved as everyone contributes to upload data and information and everyone is able to access the data whenever needed. <strong> Improved inventory </strong> monitoring is also expected to happen because the effort to monitor inventory in the warehouse has been significantly reduced. As after items are recorded in the system, people no longer have to visit the warehouse to check for stocks.<strong> Improved production planning and resource management </strong> would also occur because the system optimizes the resources available to plan the flow of production.</p>\r\n<p>After ERP implementation, <strong>better analytics</strong> is achievable as all the data are gathered into one place it becomes simpler and faster to analyze and interpret the data and information. <strong>Better analytics</strong> will lead to a better sales forecast. ERP implementation will also <strong>simplify compliance and risk management</strong> because ERP regulates all of the company’s process and compile them into one, making it easy to monitor and reduce risks while managing the company. Smooth implementation of ERP will also mean <strong>happier customers</strong>. Customers are happy when the service is fast, efficient and meet their needs. ERP enables the process faster and more efficient.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> ERP also has the benefits of reducing the production cost and facilitate the real-time decision-making system </strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>ERP plans projects and optimizes production costs according to the capacity of the facility, therefore able to produce more despite using the same amount of space. ERP is also capable of understanding the problem area &amp; requirement of the client. Relieving pains from production processes and fulfill the needs of clients. ERP can help companies in business growth. Because the system makes the company run in a more efficient manner, it becomes easier for the company to grow.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>An ERP system provider in Indonesia is PT Bisnis Sistem Indonesia (BSI). PT BSI has been successfully aligning the company’s business process into Infor LN, the ERP software that PT BSI offers. Infor LN has the capability of streamlining the workflow and controlling them at the same time. Infor LN makes communication easier, as when the data is changed other divisions are informed about it. Infor LN is guaranteed to simplify and quicken the pace of the workflow, no matter the size of the company or how many personnel that needs to be managed.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>In conclusion, enterprises need ERP to monitor the large scale production and manage risks using accurate data. This is important so that the enterprises increase their efficiency in their production process and improve productivity. ERP implementation in the enterprise could also be beneficial to the enterprise in terms of optimizing costs and facilitate decision making in real-time.</p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 86, '2020-03-16 07:17:31', 862, '', '2021-03-03 04:45:07', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 07:17:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 36, 0, 20, 'erp, erp system, software erp terbaik, erp infor ln, infor LN, infor system, infor erp, why need erp, erp benefit', 'Enterprises, a large scale business has its own sets of troubles and challenges while running the company in which ERP could solve.\r\n \r\nEnterprise is a large scale business and usually has been established for a very long time. Enterprises often offer a lot of products so, therefore; stream a lot of revenue as well.\r\n  \r\nThere are a couple of reasons why enterprises should implement the ERP system in their company', 1, 706, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(205, 330, 'Solve the Enterprise Challenges: Transactions & Report in Multiple Currencies', 'system-financial-report-in-multiple-currencies', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/banners/Banner%20Blog%20%201.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enterprises, being large companies, they are sure to have a lot of employees, suppliers, and customers. They also have a series of challenges that they face. There are more challenges when the enterprise has subsidiaries or is held by foreign countries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When enterprises manufacture, they do not rely on a single supplier. Sometimes, they even have to source raw materials from other regions or countries. These regions or countries may use a different currency than the enterprise’s home currency. Enterprises also export to other countries, when they export they may receive sales from multiple currencies.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another challenge that the enterprise may face regarding to multiple currencies is the financial report. The financial report may be required to be in the currency that the enterprise uses or the currency that the management requests. The financial report is required to be as such in spite of doing transactions in multiple currencies.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What happens if it is done manually?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When the financial report is done manually, each division such as purchasing, sales, and finance has its own calculations in an excel sheet. This may lead to miscalculations because there is no data to be referred to. Because it is done manually, the data between each division are not integrated. This could cause each division to wait for data from other divisions and compiling them manually.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These particular challenges faced by enterprises can be solved by Infor LN. Infor LN is an ERP system provided by PT BSI, a company that has been helping clients implement Infor LN into their company successfully.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">ERP could help the company in simplifying everyday transactions and aiding in making custom reports.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">ERP Infor LN has the advantage of supporting the multi-currency feature. It saves the home currency, which is the currency used in the country or region the company is located at, or the currency that the management requires to use. The software also immediately exchanges the currency when doing purchases or receiving sales, despite having transactions in multiple currencies. At the end of the month, the system will read all the transactions and compile all the transactions to aid the financial accountancy. Infor LN has the benefit of allowing flexibility of transactions in multiple currencies and adapting the report automatically to the currency that the management requests.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information about the solution please contact our phone at +6221 304 90008 or <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Whatsapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WhatsApp +628111221789</a> (Chat Only) or our email at ptbsi@ptbsi.co.id<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 86, '2020-04-22 06:49:49', 862, '', '2021-03-03 04:30:38', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2020-04-22 06:49:49', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 8, 0, 18, 'financial report system, multiple currencies, financial report, currency, erp, erp system, software erp terbaik', 'Enterprises, especially large ones may face challenges while doing transactions using multiple currencies.', 1, 554, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(206, 331, 'Solve the Enterprise Challenges: Reduce the Complexity of the Intercompany Transaction', 'reduce-complexity-intercompany-transaction', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/banners/Banner%20Blog%20%202.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"how to reduce the complexity of the intercompany transaction | ERP Infor\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enterprises are essentially a company but on a much bigger scale. Enterprises sometimes do intercompany transactions which are transaction between the parent company and its subsidiaries or other related entities. Enterprises that are manufacturing companies are the example of the company do intercompany transactions often and all are a complex process.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the automotive industry, they manufacture vehicles or modes of transportation. In a vehicle spare parts &amp; components could be over 100 pieces. One of the examples is, the machine has around 38 components and a few supporting parts to create a vehicle product</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The car assembled with so many parts will need the supplier’s help as the provider of that particular part.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Why it is not all made into 1 company?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The reason is that the company must not stock so many items, therefore the car components will be supplied by other companies or subsidiaries. For efficiency!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">This issue could pose challenges for the enterprise, financial report issue is one of them.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However, doing many intercompany transactions may cause financial report issues. When the company orders spare parts from its subsidiaries in other countries, it is without a doubt that the payments will differ from each country’s regulation. The finance team has to manage the complicated financial report due to the status of the payment whether it is considered a loan, a payment of a debt or a permanent equity agreement between the two entities. Another problem would be at what percentage does the parent company pay taxes after taking account of the subsidiaries’ sales. Because when the parent company owns a large percentage of stocks in the subsidiary company, are the sales of the subsidiary company counted as the sales of the parent company too? Furthermore, the finance team has to keep track of payments done in different currencies. Those issues could pose challenges in compiling the financial report.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Another complex issue</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Managing quality, price, the delivery time of the spare parts and fit of each spare part to the whole vehicle when built, is a complex task that should be completed in order for a smooth production process. Doing so while dealing with so many vendors is not an easy task.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The enterprise needs to accommodate if the vendor is from a different country or region in terms of funds in a different currency. The purchasing team needs to take account of vendor locations in terms of delivery time because some of them may not be near. Make sure the delivery time is on schedule so it does not affect the flow of production. If the delivery is late it may halt production.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In order to solve these challenges, there is a solution called Infor LN. Infor LN is ERP software provided by PT Bisnis Sistem Indonesia (BSI) in Indonesia that has become an ERP provider that successfully aligns the client’s company process to ERP since 1998. ERP is a software that integrates data and information, which makes it faster and more efficient to run the company process.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Infor LN is a system that collaborates information &amp; requirements from requestors to the recipient automatically. The system immediately notifies other departments if goods are received or have defects, despite the one receiving the goods are the warehouse department. The system is also able to make sure that each department’s requests and data are delivered and understood by the recipients.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Infor LN also functions as a system that captures every process of the transaction. In every process of the transaction, all the data is recorded by the software. For example, the finance team no longer has to compile the financial report in such a complicated manner as the system already tracks the transactions and is capable of converting the financial report into any currency immediately.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In conclusion, to reduce the complexity of the intercompany transaction a system that could record all transactions to simplify the creation of the financial report. Infor could be the system that reduces the complexity of intercompany transactions. Infor also has the benefits of immediately changing the financial report to the currency required.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information about the solution please contact our phone at +6221 304 90008 or <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Whatsapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WhatsApp +628111221789</a> (Chat Only) or our email at ptbsi@ptbsi.co.id<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 86, '2020-04-22 06:56:12', 862, '', '2021-03-03 04:25:44', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2020-04-23 02:34:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 10, 0, 17, 'transaction, automotive company, erp, erp system, software erp terbaik, erp infor ln, infor LN, infor system, infor erp', 'automotive companies produce goods with so many spare parts, intercompany transactions can become a complex challenge.', 1, 558, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(207, 332, 'Answering the challenge of cost analyzing in a company with technology', 'cost-analyzing-company-with-technology', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/banners/Banner%20Blog%20%203.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"challenge in analyzing cost within company\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Since enterprises are a large company, the efforts that are needed to maintain the company are enormous. This is caused by the complex company processes that are required to be done to run the company. Each division has specific tasks that they have to complete, and their result affects the decision of other departments.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the finance department, cost analysis is important. However, it is a difficult task if the finance team could not get the data needed fast and accurately. It is crucial for the company to forecast production cost and sales cost in order to set targets. The targets that are set affect the decisions regarding the projects the production team will take</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For example, when a project is currently being processed and when the demand &amp; sales request is made, the company should be able to project the sales forecast. The finance team should be aware of the cost of producing 1 unit, how many units to be produced, and production time, in order to anticipate how much money should be spent every day. Each component price, lead delivery, and terms of payment should be known to analyze the cost that needs to be spent. Therefore the accesses of information from sales &amp; purchasing that finance needs have to be fast &amp; efficient.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To determine how much money is needed to be spent every day, each department has to break down what costs do they require in order to operate. For example, the design team allocates the budget for designing software, drawing tools and electricity. Due to the requirement of collaborating with so many departments, it is not easy to get fast and accurate data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During the production process, it is not just the finance team that should be aware of the costs that are needed for production, but the whole company department must be aware of the costs needed. This is what makes it complex and challenging. Every department needs to communicate in order for a smooth production process and each department should be able to report back to the finance team regarding the money that they have spent. When the reports are not collected into one automatic system, the finance team has multiple excel sheets. Coordinating and thinking about it must have caused inconveniences.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The scenario mentioned above means that managing demands from each department should be automatic and not manual. That is due to the complexity of the process starting from the creation of demand until the payment is received.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In other words, big companies should have a system in order to analyze costs well</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">What is the appropriate system?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are a manufacturing company such as automotive, electronics, packaging, mining, oil &amp; gas and similar companies that have high complexity, it is appropriate for you to implement an ERP system in your company.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Infor LN of PT Bisnis Sistem Indonesia (BSI) could be the solution to the challenge mentioned above. Infor LN is an ERP that integrates information and data for the whole company. When the system is implemented, the moment data is inputted to the system, other departments could see it immediately in real-time. This makes it faster and more efficient to run company processes. Departments do not have to wait for each other for the data from other departments, making it time-saving and efficient.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information about the solution please contact our phone at +6221 304 90008 or <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Whatsapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WhatsApp +628111221789</a> (Chat Only) or our email at ptbsi@ptbsi.co.id<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 86, '2020-04-22 07:38:08', 862, '', '2021-03-03 04:23:38', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2020-04-23 02:43:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 7, 0, 16, 'analysis, access of information, sales forecast, erp, erp system, software erp terbaik', 'the challenges that enterprises face to analyze costs across the company in order to forecast sales.', 1, 579, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(208, 333, 'How to overcome the complex equipment configuration issue using the latest technology', 'complex-equipment-configuration-issue', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/banners/Banner%20Blog%20%204.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"configure equipement issue with the latest technology\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To produce a vehicle it requires a lot of parts. Each vehicle requires up to 100 different components. The bigger the vehicle, the more advanced, the more components that are needed. Sourcing the components alone is already a complex task, along with technological advancements the components also change or be added as well. Therefore the automotive company has to keep up with improvements in technology despite the already complex task of sourcing each and every component for mass production.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We PT Bisnis Sistem Indonesia (PT BSI) understands that vehicle production is complex, therefore we offer a solution for the automotive industry called Infor LN to overcome the challenging complexity of vehicle production. Infor LN is an ERP system that can cater to the vast amount of spare parts, quality control of the items, the fulfillment of the items, and design fit to the production result. ERP is capable of tallying up every single production process from start to finish, making every single data traceable. This is extremely useful for car manufacturing as the complex processes are able to be documented, reducing the risk of possibly missing any procedures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Other benefits of implementing Infor LN are short product life cycles, faster commissioning, and high availability stocks. The products have a shorter life cycle because Infor LN can optimize stocks inside the warehouse and orders the quantity needed exactly for mass production, therefore the stocks in the warehouse are rotating quickly. In terms of faster commissioning, Infor enables jobs to be done faster because the system integrates between departments, making it faster to approve jobs to be executed. Regarding the high availability stocks, Infor is able to enhance the production process and make it faster, making it possible to have a high availability of products.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Infor LN is trusted by Ferrari and thousands of other suppliers, meaning that Infor LN is capable of making the enterprises run at a much smoother pace. We, Infor LN believe that with lots of experience and is trusted by big brands, we are confident that we have the best practice to handle automotive industry challenges that happen in the process and operation of the automotive industry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information about the solution please contact our phone at +6221 304 90008 or <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Whatsapp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WhatsApp +628111221789</a> (Chat Only) or our email at ptbsi@ptbsi.co.id<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 86, '2020-04-22 07:46:49', 862, '', '2021-03-03 04:20:56', 863, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2021-03-02 02:07:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', 6, 0, 15, 'Complex equipment configuration issue, using the latest technology, system infor, ptbsi', 'the complex process that car manufacturers have to go through in order to produce cars is solvable through Infor LN. ', 1, 583, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0, '*', '');
